-- Bernanke’s Easing Option, Apple, Iran: Week Ahead Jan. 23-28
-- B y   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r ,   G r e g   M i l e s   a n d   K o h   K e a t   K i a n
-- 2012-01-23T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/bernanke-s-easing-option-apple-iran-week-ahead-jan-23-28.html
     Jan. 23 (Bloomberg)-- Federal Reserve Chairman Ben. S.
Bernanke may indicate a third round of large-scale asset
purchases is still an option to bolster the economy after a two-
day meeting of the Fed’s Open Market Committee. European Union
Finance Ministers will discuss the region’s sovereign debt
crisis as Germany’s Ifo survey gives a snapshot of business
sentiment in Europe’s largest economy.  EU foreign ministers are likely to authorize a phased
embargo of oil imports from  Iran .  The  World Economic Forum  takes place in Davos, Switzerland.
In the U.S., Apple Inc., Ford Motor Co. and McDonald’s Corp.
will be among companies releasing results.  The Year of the Dragon starts in  China  and other Asian
nations. Nominees for the Academy Awards will be announced.  MONDAY, Jan. 23  To contact the reporters on this story:
